Send a message to the user. Supports plain text, rich cards, interactive elements, polls, optional thread creation, and Slack blocks. Prefer rich formatting for structured or multi-part results (task outcomes, summaries, checklists, comparisons, incident/debug updates, plans): cards/interactions on Discord, blocks on Slack. In direct chat replies, prefer a native reply attached to the triggering message, but do not ping the user unless they explicitly ask for it. Set `reply_to_trigger=false` when the user explicitly wants a normal channel message instead of a reply. Set `reply_ping_user=true` only if the user explicitly wants a ping; otherwise prefer `reply_ping_user=false`.
